Week 2: Early philosophical determinism and scientific determinism (from Stoicism to classical mechanics)

Philosophical stances discussed: 
- Free will and the illusion of choice;
- How the addition of a deterministic physical framework affects our prior arguments;
- The shift from a force-centric Newtonian framework to a general Lagrangian framework for mechanics.

Recommended Readings: 
- Principia by Newton
- The System of Nature by d'Holbach
- MÃ©canique Analytique by Lagrange
- A Philosophical Essay on Probabilities by Laplace
- Norton's Dome and pushback against determinism (Intuitive https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EjZB81jCGj4)
- Mathematical derivation behind Norton's Dome (https://sites.pitt.edu/~jdnorton/Goodies/Dome/#Note%206)

Extension:
- Identifying the differences between deterministic and predictable.
